volume 15

// IMPORTANT NOTE:
// This translation file is used by the mbrola voices BR1, BR2 and BR3.
// There are very small differences between the files `ptbr` and `ptbr4`.
// Use a diff tool to check the subtle differences between these 2 files.
// The voices of the Brazilian mbrola lack many unusual pairs of phonemes.
// The compilation will fail if you put more than 255 rules in this file.

// NAVIGATION HINT:
// This file is organized in sections and blocks. Some sections have blocks.
// If you want to go to the section that has rules for the consonants, press
// UP or DOWN keys until you hear "SECTION" "OF" "CONSONANTS", or use a search tool.
// If you wanna go to the block that has specific rules for the phoneme "x",
// press UP or DOWN buttons until you hear "block" "of" "x", or use a search tool.

// CONTROL NUMBERS:
//  1: skip the next phoneme
//  2: match this and previous phoneme (backwards)
//  4: match only at the start of a word
//  8: don't match two phonemes across a word boundary
//  9: skip the next phoneme and don't match two phonemes across a word boundary
// 64: match only at the end of a word


